Preheat #air fryer{} to 375 degrees. Spray bottom of #air fryer basket{} with
@nonstick cooking spray{}. Place @Sesame Ginger Chicken Gyoza{1} in a single
layer in air fryer basket (reserve gyoza sauce packet for use in Step 2). Lightly
spray gyoza with nonstick cooking spray. Air fry gyoza until lightly browned and
warmed through, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, you may need to cook in batches depending on the size of your
> air fryer.

PAN FRYING ALTERNATIVE: Heat @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over high
heat. Add gyoza, flat sides down, and @water{1/3%cup} to pan (be careful of
splatter!); cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and cook until
water has evaporated and bottoms of gyoza are crispy, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Halve @Mini Cucumber{2} lengthwise; slice into 1⁄2-inch-thick half-moons. Tear or
roughly chop @Cilantro{1/4%oz} leaves and stems.

In a #large bowl{}, combine cucumbers, @Red Cabbage and Carrot Mix{4%oz}, @Sweet Soy Glaze{4%tbsp}, gyoza sauce, @Sesame Seeds{1%tbsp}, and half the cilantro. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to combine.

Crush @Peanuts{1/2%oz} in their package (we used a #rolling pin{}!). Transfer gyoza
to bowl with salad; toss to combine.

Divide gyoza salad between bowls. Garnish with peanuts, remaining cilantro, and
@Sriracha{1%tsp} to taste. Serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.